@thdxr I have long been first or early. I was the 79th user of Instagram. I was the first one to link to TechCrunch, to Product Hunt, and to TechMeme. 

Siri was launched in my house. I had the first ride in the first Mercedes AI car and the first ride in the first Tesla. Matic Robot was launched in my house, among many other stories like this. 

Being early is something that is often wrong, in a way. But those who are early end up with the wisdom, and wisdom (when the timing becomes right) is in short supply.

