@JuliaMarkD2 As with all painful things in life there are many lessons and gifts they bring too. 

She had a most beautiful home in Montana that looked out on Emigrant Mountain. Stunning. And I got to go to Yellowstone National Park many times because of her membership. And met many interesting people along the way. Her mechanic now runs a large printing company in Bozeman, for instance.

So it's not all bad. If she didn't have a whacky belief system she never would have moved to Montana before it was cool.
